From be54859d33b02b04c880a8ea868538823aa90399 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zach Taylor <zctaylor.work@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 13:31:39 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 20/48] Add warp.ui.toast + warp.keymap.bind (oh-my-warp)

Two host->app plugin APIs that need an AppContext: warp.ui.toast(message, kind?)
and warp.keymap.bind(commandId, keys). The IPC handler enqueues a PluginAppRequest
onto a channel that the PluginHost model drains via spawn_stream_local on the
foreground executor (app/src/plugin/app_requests.rs), where it shows a toast
(ToastStack) or registers an editable binding. Keybindings dispatch a new
WorkspaceAction::RunPluginCommand(id) handled by the Workspace, which runs the
plugin command (shared commands::run_plugin_command). See PLUGIN_SPEC.md (M3).
